text: The Sárospatak District (Hungarian: Sárospataki járás) is a district in the northeastern part of Borsod-Abaúj-Zemplén County. Sárospatak is also the name of the town where the district seat is found. Its population in 2022 was 21,154. == Municipalities == The district has 1 town and 15 villages. * Bodrogolaszi * Erdőhorváti * Györgytarló * Háromhuta * Hercegkút * Kenézlő * Komlóska * Makkoshotyka * Olaszliszka * Sárazsadány * Sárospatak – district seat * Tolcsva * Vajdácska * Vámosújfalu * Viss * Zalkod The bolded municipality is the city.
